IMPLEMENT SUBSTITUTION TECHNIQUE USING CAESAR CIPHER
Date:


AIM

To implement Caesar Cipher technique for encryption and decryption of a given text using a shift value in C.
ALGORITHM
Step 1: Start the program
Step 2: Read the input values for text and shift value(1-25). Step 3: Read the user’s choice.
Step 4: For Encrypting and Decrypting each character in the text:

	•	Check if the character is an alphabet.
	•	If uppercase, set base = 'A' or lowercase, set base = 'a'.
	•	If choice = 1 (Encrypt):
Replace character using
(character − base + shift) % 26 + base
	•	If choice = 2 (Decrypt):
Replace character using
(character − base − shift + 26) % 26 + base
	•	If any choice value other than 1 and 2 then display “Invalid Choice” Step 5: Display the resulting encrypted and decrypted text.
Sep 6: Stop the execution

PROGRAM CODING
#include <stdio.h> 
#include <stdlib.h>
#include <string.h>
#include <ctype.h>

// Function to encrypt text using Caesar Cipher 
void encrypt(char *text, int shift)
{
for (int i = 0; text[i] != '\0'; i++)
{
char ch = text[i]; if (isalpha(ch)) {
char base = isupper(ch) ? 'A' : 'a'; 
text[i] = (ch - base + shift) % 26 + base;
}
}
}


// Function to decrypt text using Caesar Cipher 
void decrypt(char *text, int shift) {
for (int i = 0; text[i] != '\0'; i++) { 
char ch = text[i];
if (isalpha(ch)) {
char base = isupper(ch) ? 'A' : 'a';
text[i] = (ch - base - shift + 26) % 26 + base;
}
}
}
int main( ) {
char text[256]; int shift, choice;
printf("=== Caesar Cipher in C ===\n"); 
printf("Enter text (max 255 chars): ");

scanf(“%s”,text);
printf("Enter shift value (1-25): ");
scanf("%d", &shift);
while(1)
{
printf("Choose operation:\n1. Encrypt\n2. Decrypt\n Enter choice: ");
scanf("%d", &choice);
if (choice == 1)
{
encrypt(text, shift);
printf("Encrypted text: %s\n", text);
}
else if (choice ==2)
{
decrypt(text, shift);
printf("Decrypted text: %s\n", text);
}
else
{
printf("Invalid Choice");
exit(1);
}
}
return 0;
}







