IMPLEMENT TRANSPOSITION TECHNIQUE USING RAILFENCE ROW & COLUMN TRANSFORMATION
Date:


AIM
To write a C program to implement the rail fence row & Column Transposition
technique.
ALGORITHM

STEP 1: Start the program

STEP 2: Read the input string.

STEP 3: Find the length of the string.

STEP 4: Encryption:

	•	Take characters at even positions and store them first.
	•	Then take characters at odd positions and append them.
	•	Display the ciphertext. STEP 5: Decryption:
	•	Divide the ciphertext into two halves.
	•	Place first half characters in even positions.
	•	Place second half characters in odd positions.
	•	Form the original text. STEP 6: Display the decrypted text. STEP 7: Stop the execution

PROGRAM CODING
#include<stdio.h>
#include<string.h>
#include<stdlib.h> 
void main()
{
int i,j,k,l;
char a[20],c[20],d[20];
printf("\n\t\t RAIL FENCE TECHNIQUE"); 
printf("\n\n Enter the input string:");
scanf("%s",a);
l=strlen(a);
for(i=0,j=0;i<l;i++)
{
if(i%2==0) 
c[j++]=a[i];
}
for(i=0;i<l;i++)
{
if(i%2==1) 
c[j++]=a[i];
}
printf("\nCipher text after applying rail fence :");
printf("\n%s",c);
if(l%2==0)
k=(l/2);
else
k=(l/2)+1;
for(i=0,j=0;i<k;i++)
{
d[j]=c[i]; 
j=j+2;
}

for(i=k,j=1;i<l;i++)
{
d[j]=c[i];
j=j+2;
}
d[l]='\0';
printf("\n text after decryption:");
printf("%s",d);
}
